HEADWORD: Succussation
<hw>Suc`cus*sa"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>succussare</ets> to jolt, v. intens. fr. <ets>succutere</ets>,
<ets>succussum</ets>, to fling up from below, to toss up; <ets>sub</ets>
under + <ets>quatere</ets> to shake.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A trot or
trotting.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A shaking; succussion.</def>⟦br⟧
